POWER BI PASTEABLE VISUAL CODE
For Deneb custom visual in Power BI

Use this when your Excel data has already been loaded into Power BI.
This file does not create data tables. It only creates visuals.

Power BI cannot create native visuals from one pasted TXT file.
To paste visual code directly, install the Deneb custom visual:
Power BI Desktop > Visualizations > Get more visuals > Search "Deneb"

Then add one Deneb visual per block below and paste the JSON into Deneb.

============================================================
VISUAL 1 - EXECUTIVE PRODUCT RETURN SCATTER
============================================================

Add these fields to the Deneb visual dataset:
- Products[Company]
- Products[ProductName]
- Products[IndexName]
- Products[Currency]
- Products[CohortNo]
- Products[ParticipationRate]
- Products[CapRate]
- Products[FloorRate]
- Products[IndexBaseValue]
- Return From Cohort Base
- Participated Return
- Credited Return
- Risk Score

Paste this JSON into Deneb:

{
  "$schema": "https://vega.github.io/schema/vega-lite/v5.json",
  "background": "#F7F8FA",
  "autosize": {
    "type": "fit",
    "contains": "padding"
  },
  "data": {
    "name": "dataset"
  },
  "transform": [
    {
      "calculate": "datum['ProductName'] + ' | C' + datum['CohortNo']",
      "as": "CohortLabel"
    },
    {
      "calculate": "datum['Risk Score'] >= 70 ? 'High' : datum['Risk Score'] >= 40 ? 'Medium' : 'Low'",
      "as": "RiskBand"
    }
